            <langmaterial id="ref53" label="Language of Materials note">Collection is primarily in English; materials in German, Japanese, and Norwegian are indicated at the file level.</langmaterial>
            <abstract id="ref61" label="Collection Overview">The Rick Miller Papers span the years 1970-1988. The collection consists of documents collected by Miller while he was a production manager for the following artists: Aerosmith, Eric Carmen, Christopher Cross, ELO, Fleetwood Mac, The Jacksons, Ted Nugent, Lou Reed, The Rolling Stones, Santana, Bob Seger, Boz Scaggs, and Robin Trower. The papers document the featured tours rather than the artists and include riders, blueprints, stage plans, venue information, venue photographs, and lighting cues, as well as itineraries for artists and crew, correspondence, contracts, artist requests, and carnets (merchandise passports). The collection is arranged alphabetically by artist, and then chronologically by tour.</abstract>
        </did>
        <bioghist id="ref51">
            <head>Biographical/Historical note</head>
            <p>Rick Miller is a production manager, whose work in the 1970s and 1980s encompassed extensive concert touring.</p>
            <p></p>
        </bioghist>
